TITLE: Manually Tracking View Navigation in React Native with Datadog RUM
DESCRIPTION: Code example demonstrating how to manually track view navigation in a React Native application using Datadog RUM's startView and stopView methods, including passing custom attributes.
SOURCE: https://github.com/datadog/dd-sdk-reactnative/blob/develop/packages/core/README.md#2025-04-22_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import {
    DdSdkReactNative,
    DdSdkReactNativeConfiguration,
    DdLogs,
    DdRum
} from '@datadog/mobile-react-native';

// Start a view with a unique view identifier, a custom view url, and an object to attach additional attributes to the view
DdRum.startView('ViewKey', 'ViewName', Date.now(), {
    'custom.foo': 'something'
});
// Stops a previously started view with the same unique view identifier, and an object to attach additional attributes to the view
DdRum.stopView('ViewKey', Date.now(), { 'custom.bar': 42 });
```

